ip_description:
Researchers at UC San Diego have developed a novel treatment strategy for ARVC. Using a mouse ARVC model which carries mutations in a specific gene, our researchers show that using an AAV (adenoviral vector) carrying the wild-type gene under the control of a cardiac-specific promoter the treated mice:

a) significantly improved ejection fractions, end-diastolic volumes, and end-systolic volumes;

b) improved electrical function (improved QRS duration and less premature ventricular contractions);

c) had significantly reduced cardiac fibrosis;

d) significantly improved survival;

e) even at a late disease stage had improved cardiac function, improved cell-cell junction proteins, and prevented mortality;

f) preserved the cell-cell junction and cardiac function several months post-treatment.
